description:
Promotional info from DC - &quot;Robin III: Cry of the Huntress was a six-issue bi-weekly limited series published from December of 1992 until March of 1993. Like many comics of the early 1990s, this series was distributed in both a newsstand edition, and a polybagged direct market edition, which included special cover enhancements. The cover enhancement was described as a &quot;moving cover&quot;. This series also helped to establish the background and supporting cast members that would appear in the ongoing Robin comic book series as well as reintroducing the Huntress.&quot;

From Comicvine - &quot;This is the final mini-series in the trilogy from Chuck Dixon (following Robin &amp; Robin II: Joker's Wild). This mini series paired up new Robin Tim Drake with The Huntress as they take on the KGBeast. The issues came in both regular versions and bagged versions with a moving hologram cover.

The mini-series were popular enough to lead into a new Robin ongoing the following year, which would end up lasting 183 issues from 1993 until 2009.&quot;

Well, you don't get the cool moving covers, but this is a good mini worth checking out for Tim Drake and Huntress fans. All six issues are presented in digital copies by Klingon Empire. Please seed, and enjoy! :-)
